From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: AgentOS Tests <tests@agentos.invalid>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 23:30:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] fstests: require fsx at the test that invokes it

The AgentOS bootstrap defers test-local tool checks so missing ports become
strict per-test notruns. generic/075 invoked fsx without such a gate, turning
the missing port into misleading result-file errors.

---
 tests/generic/075 | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/tests/generic/075 b/tests/generic/075
index ce6f4bc4..04ef5810 100755
--- a/tests/generic/075
+++ b/tests/generic/075
@@ -103,5 +103,6 @@ _process_args()
 
 _require_test
+_require_command "$FSX_PROG" fsx
 
 size10=`expr 10 \* 1024 \* 1024`	# 10 megabytes
 filelen=$size10
-- 
2.43.0
